raged the God that wears the silver Bow , And his broad Eyes with sparkling Fury glow , Descended Phoebus in a burning Ray , His beamy Locks declares the Prince of Day , And flashing Glories round his Temples play , Each on his Face the trembling Victims fall , Their stammering Tongues would fain for Mercy call
his broad Eyes with sparkling Fury glow
